cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically in the area of motion-based object segmentation using dense RGB-D scene flow. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves deep neural networks, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of robotics and manipulation scenarios suggests cs.RO (Robotics and Control) as another likely category. Finally, the generation of a synthetic dataset involves computer graphics, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics).
